<TITLE> BDR probe misses another deadline </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 21 (bdnews24.com)  The BDR mutiny investigation report missed another submission deadline on Wednesday. The police have so far missed at least 10 deadlines to submit the probe report regarding the BDR mutiny of Feb 25-26, 2009 in Pilkhana, Dhaka. The bloody rebellion killed about 70 people with 57 army officers deputed to the paramilitary border security force. AKM Enamul Haque, a chief metropolitan magistrate, fixed the next date of submitting the report on May 19. Abdul Kahar Akhand, a special superintendent of CID, is investigating the case. At first the case was filed with Lalbagh Police Station for murder, loot and arson. Then it was transferred to the New Market Police Station. A former MP of BNP, Nasiruddin Ahmed Pintu, and an Awami League leader Torab Ali were arrested in this case. About 2,264 BDR soldiers were shown arrested in the case. Another 34 persons not professionally affiliated with BDR were also shown arrested. Of them 2,240 people were taken to remand for questioning and 533 gave their statements to the court. 
